🔷 Snapshot Testing

Snapshot testing checks if UI changes unexpectedly.

📌 Uses Jest

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Example Snapshot Test

```jsx
import renderer from "react-test-renderer";
import Button from "./Button";

test("matches snapshot", () => {
  const tree = renderer.create(<Button />).toJSON();
  expect(tree).toMatchSnapshot();
});
```

📌 First time → snapshot file created
📌 If UI changes → test fails

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 When to Use Snapshot Testing?

✔ Small UI components
✔ Static components
✔ Prevent accidental UI changes

❌ Avoid for large dynamic components

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Testing API Calls

```jsx
test("fetches data", async () => {
  render(<FetchComponent />);
  
  const items = await screen.findByText("User Name");
  expect(items).toBeInTheDocument();
});
```

📌 Use async/await
📌 Use `findBy` queries

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Best Queries in React Testing Library

| Query          | Use            |
| -------------- | -------------- |
| getByText      | Find by text   |
| getByRole      | Find by role   |
| getByLabelText | Form inputs    |
| findByText     | Async elements |

📌 Prefer `getByRole` (best practice ⭐)

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Good Testing Principles

✔ Test behavior, not implementation
✔ Test what user sees
✔ Avoid testing internal state
✔ Write small tests
✔ Keep tests readable

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

⚠️ Common Testing Mistakes

❌ Testing implementation details
❌ Using too many snapshots
❌ Ignoring accessibility
❌ Over-mocking everything

